    "chemicalDescription": [
      "r-(s-HIV-1 Oligopeptide-5 rh-Oligopeptide-98 Pentapeptide-79 rh-Oligopeptide-108 rh-Oligopeptide-100 rh-Oligopeptide-101) a single chain fusion peptide, produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the genes encoding for s-HIV-1 Oligopeptide-5 SP, rh-Oligopeptide-98, Pentapeptide-79, rh-Oligopeptide-108, rh-Oligopeptide-100 and rh-Oligopeptide-101. The fusion peptide contains 252 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
    ],
